        public GetTransactionsDTO(Account account,
                  java.util.Calendar date)
        creates a GetTransactionsDTO. Note that the date is converted to a Period; this means that it is truncated to 0:00:00 the next day. If you definitely need time and date, use the constructor with period and set Period.setUseTime(true) before passing it.
